easy choc chip cookies i need a recipe for choc chip cookies nothing too hard plz ingredients cups all purpose flour teaspoon baking soda teaspoon salt cup unsalted butter melted cup packed brown sugar cup white sugar tablespoon vanilla extract egg egg yolk cups semisweet chocolate chips directions preheat the oven to degrees f degrees c grease cookie sheets or line with parchment paper sift together the flour baking soda and salt set aside in a medium bowl cream together the melted butter brown sugar and white sugar until well blended beat in the vanilla egg and egg yolk until light and creamy mix in the sifted ingredients until just blended stir in the chocolate chips by hand using a wooden spoon drop cookie dough cup at a time onto the prepared cookie sheets cookies should be about inches apart bake for to minutes in the preheated oven or until the edges are lightly toasted cool on baking sheets for a few minutes before transferring to wire racks to cool completely Cookie Ice cream Chocolate Jewish cuisine Chocolate Salty Balls Flour Cooking weights and measures Rice pudding Japanese cuisine Mayonnaise Coffee Pancake Cold Stone Creamery Haggis Breakfast Souffl__ Pizza Recipe Halva Cuisine of Denmark Vinegar Sandwich Tea Oreo Bacon Biscuit Baked Alaska Cuisine of Brazil German cuisine Tortilla Milkshake Cheesecake Kraft Dinner Peanut butter Cookware and bakeware Sushi Idli Chili con carne Pop-Tarts Hot dog Twix Spoon Brewery Potato Cuisine of the Philippines Egg (food) Mooncake Full English breakfast Potato chips Custard Polish cuisine Maple syrup Dim sum Cocoa Tofu Ramen Turkish coffee Baking French toast Muffin Girl Scout cookies Cuisine of Singapore Cha chaan teng Paint Glass Breadmaker Dairy Vegetarian cuisine Bengali cuisine Wine Confectionery Soft drink Soul food Cantonese cuisine Soup Scrambled eggs Peruvian cuisine Vanilla Bearnaise sauce Dumpling In-N-Out Burger Soap Barbecue Mouth ulcer Welding Wok D__ner kebab Cuisine of Argentina Risotto Kit Kat Medica